cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.CG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with reconstructing 3D scenes from multiple views, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on representing the 3D scene using structured representations of curves and surfaces, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions evaluating the results on synthetic and real datasets, which suggests the use of machine learning (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) techniques.
